  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b86\u0baa\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc7 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 2 \u0baa\u0bc6\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd, 3 \u0b86\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b89\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f 5 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb9\u0bb0\u0bcb\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "5 people including 2 women, 3 men from the same family who stole gold ornaments in Batticaloa arrested with heroin",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "On Monday (25) 5 people, including 2 women and 3 men belonging to the same family, who broke into a house and robbed 8 quarter pounds of gold jewelery in the Ebravoor area of \u200b\u200bBatticaloa, were arrested and heroin was recovered from the arrested two men and one woman, said the Ebravoor police.",
        "Ebravur R.C. The owner of a house on the street locked the house at 11.00 am on the day of the incident and went out with his family. When he returned home at 9.15 pm that day, the back door of the house was broken and 8 feet of gold ornaments were stolen from the cupboard in the room of the house.",
        "After a complaint was made to the police in this regard, the investigation conducted by the police led by the officer-in-charge of crime prevention unit of Ebravoor police station, on Monday (25) revealed that two men and two women aged 20 and 45 years of age belonging to the same family from Michu Nagar area; They arrested 5 people including",
        "The police recovered heroin from a woman and 2 men who were arrested and recovered the stolen gold ornaments from them and during the investigation they conducted a 3 and a half pound gold chain which was pawned in a jewelery shop in Batticaloa and recovered 8 quarter pounds of stolen gold jewellery."
      ],
